<DocsLayout title="Plugin Development" section="plugins">
  <h1>Plugin Development</h1>

  <p>*ARRgh!'s source plugins are esbuild-bundled TypeScript modules that implement a simple HTTP API. The plugin host loads them and proxies requests from the .NET server.</p>

  <h2>Plugin protocol</h2>

  <p>A plugin exposes these endpoints over HTTP:</p>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Endpoint</th><th>Required</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>GET /info</code></td><td>Yes</td><td>Plugin metadata — <code>id</code>, <code>name</code>, <code>content_types</code>, <code>default_explicit</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>GET /manga/:source_id/chapters</code></td><td>Yes</td><td>Chapter list for a title</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>GET /chapter/:source_id/pages</code></td><td>Yes (comics)</td><td>Image URLs for a chapter</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>GET /chapter/:source_id/text</code></td><td>Yes (novels)</td><td>Markdown text for a novel chapter</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <p>Plugins are <strong>download-only</strong>. Search, covers, and metadata come from the discover fan-out authorities (MangaUpdates, AniList, MangaDex, NovelUpdates, WuxiaWorld, nhentai) — plugins do not need to implement <code>/search</code> or <code>/meta</code>.</p>

  <h2>Minimal plugin scaffold</h2>

  <pre><code set:text={scaffold} /></pre>

  <h2>Cloudflare-protected sources</h2>

  <p>Plugins that need to bypass Cloudflare can access the CloakBrowser stealth Chromium instance via the <code>getBrowser()</code> helper provided by the plugin host:</p>

  <pre><code set:text={browserSnippet} /></pre>

  <h2>Build and install</h2>

  <pre><code set:text={buildSnippet} /></pre>

  <h2>Distributing via the plugin index</h2>

  <p>Community plugins can be listed in the <a href="https://github.com/t2vi/arrgh/blob/main/plugin-index/index.json" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">plugin index</a> so users can browse and install them from Settings. Open a PR to add your plugin.</p>
</DocsLayout>
